abstract: Julian Assange should not be extradited to the United States as he would not get a fair trial and would be a suicide risk, his lawyer told a British court hearing on Monday.
snippet: Julian Assange should not be extradited to the United States as he would not get a fair trial and would be a suicide risk, his lawyer told a British court hearing on Monday.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Julian Assange should not be extradited to the United States as he would not get a fair trial and would be a suicide risk, his lawyer told a British court hearing on Monday.
headline_main: Assange Would Be Suicide Risk if Extradited to U.S., His Lawyer Says
headline_print_headline: Assange Would Be Suicide Risk if Extradited to U.S., His Lawyer Says

abstract: The Supreme Court said Monday it will hear a dispute over a Philadelphia Catholic agency that won't place foster children with same-sex couples, a big test of religious rights on a more conservative court.
snippet: The Supreme Court said Monday it will hear a dispute over a Philadelphia Catholic agency that won't place foster children with same-sex couples, a big test of religious rights on a more conservative court.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Supreme Court said Monday it will hear a dispute over a Philadelphia Catholic agency that won't place foster children with same-sex couples, a big test of religious rights on a more conservative court.
headline_main: Justices to Hear Philly Dispute Over Same-Sex Foster Parents
headline_print_headline: Justices to Hear Philly Dispute Over Same-Sex Foster Parents

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump on Monday managed to mangle his pronunciation of several Indian names and a Hindi word on an otherwise successful first day of his state visit to India.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump on Monday managed to mangle his pronunciation of several Indian names and a Hindi word on an otherwise successful first day of his state visit to India.
lead_paragraph: AHMEDABAD, India — U.S. President Donald Trump on Monday managed to mangle his pronunciation of several Indian names and a Hindi word on an otherwise successful first day of his state visit to India.
headline_main: Trump Stumbles on Indian Names, Hindi Word in Cricket Stadium Speech
headline_print_headline: Trump Stumbles on Indian Names, Hindi Word in Cricket Stadium Speech

abstract: President Trump joined Prime Minister Narendra Modi of India for a campaign-style rally in a 110,000-seat cricket stadium before visiting the Taj Mahal as part of a two-day visit.

abstract: President Trump was feted with music, dancers and more than 100,000 cheering attendees — if not the 10 million he says he was promised.
snippet: President Trump was feted with music, dancers and more than 100,000 cheering attendees — if not the 10 million he says he was promised.
lead_paragraph: AHMEDABAD, India — President Trump began a two-day visit to India by joining Prime Minister Narendra Modi for a campaign-style rally in a 110,000-seat cricket stadium that illustrated the populist bond between the two men and impressed a president who revels in spectacle.

abstract: The WikiLeaks founder appeared in a London court to fight attempts by the American authorities to make him answer charges of espionage.
snippet: The WikiLeaks founder appeared in a London court to fight attempts by the American authorities to make him answer charges of espionage.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — The United States government began laying out its extradition case against Julian Assange, the WikiLeaks founder, in court on Monday by arguing that he had put lives at risk and was no better than an “ordinary” criminal.
